value.value: Median nerve that exits the dorsal part of abdominal neuromere 5 (Santos et al., 2006). It does not possess a swelling at its base (Santos et al., 2006), and bifurcates more distally than more anterior nerves, to form two transverse nerves (Gorczyca et al., 1994).

Median nerve that exits the dorsal part of abdominal neuromere 6 (Santos et al., 2006). It does not possess a swelling at its base (Santos et al., 2006), and bifurcates more distally than more anterior nerves, to form two transverse nerves (Gorczyca et al., 1994).

Median nerve that exits the dorsal part of abdominal neuromere 7 (Santos et al., 2006). It does not possess a swelling at its base (Santos et al., 2006), and bifurcates more distally than more anterior nerves, to form two transverse nerves (Gorczyca et al., 1994).
Median nerve of abdominal segment 8, it bifurcates more distally than more anterior nerves, to form two transverse nerves (Gorczyca et al., 1994).

definition.value: Not clear from Santos et al. (2006) - FBrf0195119 whether this exists in third instar.

value.value: Nerve of larval abdominal segment 8 that has features of both the intersegmental and segmental nerves of more anterior segments (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). This nerve has three roots, in a pattern corresponding the roots of the segmental and intersegmental nerves of A1-7 (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). Its proximal section is closely attached to the abdominal 9 nerve (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). It carries motor neurons that innervate the ventral longitudinal and lateral transverse muscles of A8, and sensory neurons innervating the spiracular hairs and the A8 sensilla (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).
Any sensory neuron (FBbt:00005124) that has its soma located in some larval abdominal segment 8 (FBbt:00001755).
Larval sensory neuron that innervates the dorsal trichoid sensillum ALSOh. There is one of these on each side, found in abdominal segment 9.
Larval sensory neuron that innervates the dorsal trichoid sensillum ALSOp. There are three of these per ALSOp sensillum, which is found in abdominal segment 8.
Sensory neuron that innervates the DMSOp sensillum, which is found in larval abdominal segment 8.
Sensory neuron that innervates the lateral chordotonal organ lch3 of larval abdominal segment 8.
Sensory neuron whose long dendrite innervates spiracular trichoid sensillum 1 (spiracular hair 1).
Sensory neuron whose long dendrite innervates spiracular trichoid sensillum 2 (spiracular hair 2).
Sensory neuron whose long dendrite innervates spiracular trichoid sensillum 3 (spiracular hair 3).
Sensory neuron whose long dendrite innervates spiracular trichoid sensillum 4 (spiracular hair 4).

Larval multidendritic neuron with its soma in a lateral region of abdominal segment 8, in the niche between the lateral transverse muscle LT1 and the epidermis (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). There are around 3-4 of these on each side (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

Larval multidendritic neuron with its soma in a ventral region of abdominal segment 8, at the level of the ventral acute muscles (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). There are around 3-4 of these on each side (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

Nerve of larval abdominal segment 9 that has features of both the intersegmental and segmental nerves of more anterior segments (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). It has two roots and its proximal section is closely attached to the abdominal 8 nerve (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). After passing beneath the gut suspensor muscles, it gives off a thick recurrent branch, the hindgut nerve, which innervates the hindgut (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). Its main branch continues dorsoposteriorly and gives off a motor branch that innervates the A9 terminal oblique muscles (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). A posterior branch carries sensory axons from the anal sense organ and a dorsal branch carries axons of motor and sensory neurons of A9 (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).
Any sensory neuron (FBbt:00005124) that has its soma located in some larval abdominal segment 9 (FBbt:00001756).
Sensory neuron that innervates the PLSOh sensillum, which is found in larval abdominal segment 9.
Sensory neuron that innervates the lateral chordotonal organ lch3/1 of larval abdominal segment 9.
Multidendritic neuron of the ventral region of larval abdominal segment 9. There are several of these neurons.
Any sensory neuron (FBbt:00005124) that has its soma located in some larval abdominal segment 10 (FBbt:00001757).
Neuron that innervates the anal sense organ (ASO), which is found in larval abdominal segment 10.
Larval sensory neuron that innervates the basiconic (peg) sensillum of the anal sense organ. It is a bipolar dendrite neuron (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

A group of small, interconnected ganglia in the embryo or larva situated posterior to and between the two brain hemispheres and associated with the pharynx, esophagus, proventriculus and dorsal pouch.

A small paired ganglion of the embryonic and larval stomatogastric nervous system. At embryonic stage 17, it consists of approximately 25-30 neurons that form a U-shaped ganglion wedged between the anterior aspect of the brain hemispheres and the dorsal pharynx, and that have formed axons. The somata of the neurons surround a sparse neuropil domain and are enclosed in a glial sheath. Lateral projections from these neurons form the frontal connective. Medial projections that turn anteriorly on reaching the midline form the frontal nerve. Medial projections that turn posteriorly on reaching the midline form the recurrent nerve.

definition.value: The term parapharyngeal ganglion was previously used to designate the frontal ganglion (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

value.value: Unpaired larval nerve that travels in the median cleft between the dorsal pharyngeal muscles (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). Fine fibers from this nerve innervate these muscles (Schoofs et al., 2010). It is connected to the frontal ganglion (frontal nerve junction) (Schoofs et al., 2010).

Embryonic or larval nerve connecting the frontal ganglion to the hypocerebral and paraesophageal ganglia. It contains approximately 50 neuronal projections and is surrounded by flattened cells - probably glia.

Small ganglion of the embryonic or larval stomatogastric nervous system. At embryonic stage 17, it is located on the left hand side of the embryo, between the two brain hemispheres and behind the supraesophageal commissure. It is more compact than the paraesophageal ganglion and occupies a more dorsal position. It contains approximately 10-12 neurons.

Small ganglion of the embryonic/larval stomatogastric nervous system located on the right hand side of the larva, between the two brain hemispheres, behind the supraesophageal commissure. It is elongated, less compact than the hypoesophageal ganglion and occupies a more ventral position, closely attached to the esophageal wall. It contains 10-12 neurons.

Nerve of the embryo/larva that extends posteriorly from the paraesophageal ganglion, on the right side, following the convexity of the curved esophagus, and innervates the visceral muscle layering that cover the proventriculus.

Nerve of the embryo/larva that extends posteriorly from the hypocerebral ganglion, on the left side, to reach the ventricular ganglion. It then extends posteriorly to terminate on the proventricular wall.

A cluster of about 10 neurons whose somata are associated with the embryonic/larval proventriculus. Short axons projecting posteriorly from this structure fan out over the surface of the proventriculus.
Any sense organ of the larva.
A cluster of sense organs on a protuberance on either side of the anterior tip of the larval head. It contains the dorsal organ, the terminal organ and the ventral organ.
Innervated cuticular specialization just inside the larval mouth.

definition.value: This could correspond to epipharyngeal sense organ.

value.value: Any larval sense organ (FBbt:00002639) that is part of some ocular segment (FBbt:00000005).

Papilla of the dorsolateral group of the terminal organ, on the head of the embryo/larva. It is located more medially than the dorsolateral papilla and the spot sensillum of the dorsolateral group. This sensillum is innervated by three dendrites, from gustatory receptor neuron B1, B2 and B3 (Rist and Thum, 2017).
Lateralmost of the three dorsal fold medial sensilla, found more dorsal than sensillum 2 (Singh and Singh, 1984).
Ventralmost of the three dorsal fold medial sensilla, found medial to sensillum 1 and lateral to sensillum 3 (Singh and Singh, 1984).
Medialmost of the three dorsal fold medial sensilla, found more dorsal than sensillum 2 (Singh and Singh, 1984).

Sensillum of the internal dorsal fold of the larval pharynx found in a relatively lateral position (Singh and Singh, 1984). There is one of these per side, innervated by a single dendrite (Singh and Singh, 1984).
Any larval sense organ (FBbt:00002639) that is part of some labral segment (FBbt:00000008).
Monoscolopidial chordotonal organ located immediately posterior to the dorsal pharyngeal organ. Its neuron fasciculates with the labral nerve.

Sensillum of the larval head that is located proximal to the dorsal pharyngeal sense organ along the labral nerve (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997; Gendre et al., 2004). It is innervated by 5 neurons (Gendre et al., 2004; Stewart et al., 2015).
Any larval sense organ (FBbt:00002639) that is part of some antennal segment (FBbt:00000009).

An external compound sense organ of the antenno-maxillary complex of the larval head consisting of two sensilla, a dome shaped cuticular process, and a region surrounding the base of the dome (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997; Komarov and Sprecher, 2022). Each dome sensillum is innervated by seven circularly arranged triplets of olfactory receptor neuron dendrites (Komarov and Sprecher, 2022). Eleven sensory neurons of other modalities innervate six sensilla of each base region (Komarov and Sprecher, 2022; Richter et al., 2024).

Sensillum of the dorsal organ that forms a ring surrounding the dome sensillum (Komarov and Sprecher, 2022). It houses the sensory dendrites of gustatory and thermosensory neurons (Komarov and Sprecher, 2022).
Chordotonal organ with a single scolopidium.
Any sense organ (FBbt:00005155) that is part of some intercalary segment (FBbt:00000010).
